\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid13840783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Could you give your name and address please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Mrs Laura Hughes, Artro, Llanfrothen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You've married haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I'm a widow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When did you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh 1923. December of 1923.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When were you born and where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I was born in - June, 19 - 18 - 1898.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 In Danwdeg, Llanfrothen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How long did you live in Danwdeg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I lived there from when I was born - until 1923.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Where did you go to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh, I went to some rooms in Penrhyn Dydrah, for about a year. And then after that I went to live in Mant Dwr Oer over the River Glas lyn.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was that just a house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that was a house. On the way to Beddgelert. And then I came back here to live in Catherine Terrace, Llanfrothen. I was back by about
 1926. We came back to the village to live you see, because before that there hadn't been a house available in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you live there 'til you came here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When did you come here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I've been here since 1934.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember why you made the moves you did? Your family didn't make any moves did they, it was only you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, well we made moves because we wanted to move house. That's why we came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You wanted a more modern house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 That was the reason why we came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I had one brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Who was the oldes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I was, I was three years older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I could tell you how old he was when he died. He was eighty-seven, and that was in 1954.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh from Llanfrothen. Rhyd Llanfrothen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 He was a quarry worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What did he do in the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 He dressed the slates. You know, there's a word for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he split them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes, there's another word though. You know, dressing. He - he worked above ground he didn't work in - inside at all. He didn't work in the - in the - in the hole at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he have any jobs before or after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No he didn't, except that - in his home was a small - at his home there was a small farm and he used to help a bit there. But he started to work in the quarry when he was twelve, and then he used to help 
his father in the evenings with the few cattle that they had, and with the hay and things. That was up in Rhyd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember your father out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I remember it many times. I remember with the - the freeze up you know, and the - the q
uarry was shut. And another time - the quarry was shut for months. I can't tell you when that was though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know why the quarry was shut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I think that the - demand for the slates had fallen you see. That's as far as I understand it. There was no demand for the slates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you talk about the freeze up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that was when - you know, there was snow and frost. And there were whole quarries froze up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Which year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 It was about the hardest year they had. No, I can't r
emember - except that because of this snow he was home for six weeks when I was very small, he didn't go up there at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 She was sixty-eight when she died. And that was in 1940.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh from Llanfrothen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she have a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, with her aunt. Her aunt lived in that think}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 house over there, and she had a bit of a farm and she used to help - with the farming. In fact they had - a farm and - you
 know, what we call a narrow house, and another house in - in the village. In Garreg. Llanfrothen's the parish, Garreg is a small village. And she worked there after she left school until she married when she was seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she work after she got married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, not at all,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 She didn't have any part time jobs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know how many rooms there were in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes. There were two bedrooms and a living room bigger than this one and a small kitchen, and that was all. And the toilet was outside.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did anyone else live with you, apart form your brother and your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, there were twins. I think they lived for about - just over a year. But they both died. And there was - a little child 
that died before I was born. The twins were - youngest. I do remember - the twins. And I also remember the birth of my brother who was - I was three at the time. But there was only me and my brother really, who lived with my mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, she didn't. No, they were too poor for that. I mean it was the life of a quarryman, they hardly got any money at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they send the washing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, they did it all. Very few people sent washing out in those days. Only somebody who was quite well off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if your mother or father made or mended the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No they didn't. My mother used to knit and make socks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 She didn't make clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she mend them though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, she mended them. She had to mend everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you get new clothes or secondhand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well we used to get new ones but - they came very rarely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Where did you buy clothes as a rule?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, wel
l I think we must have got them in Penrhyn Deudraeth. I can't be sure you know except where we bought groceries. There wasn't a clothes shop here in the village. It must have been either Port Madoc or Penrhyn Deudraeth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was there a special time in the year when you got new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, before the gamantha.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your father make or mend your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have new shoes all the time or secondhand ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, we didn't have new ones, but we didn't have to war the
m until they were, you know, unfit to wear. They never became rags. And we got shoes when we really needed them. New shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You didn't have secondhand shoes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you buy them in Penrhyn or Port Madoc too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes,
 that's right. In fact - yes, I know we got - shoes in Penrhyn Deudraeth because the man who used to sell shoes in Penrhyn used to come }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 roun}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 d and - and collect shoes for repairs as well. You know, he'd come round and take shoes away from peoples houses and take them away to mend. His daughter's in fact in - in the sh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 p in Penrhyn, you know, Humphrey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know if your father helped your mother with jobs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, he did, a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Cleaning and cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes he did. I didn't - don't say he did a lot of washing but - you know, he did by the end certainly because she had rheumatism very badly. 'Course she couldn't do her work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about decorating and repairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well my mother used to do the decorating herself. She never used to pay anyone to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about improving the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well I can't remember that we had to have any improvements done. 'Cos the man next door owned the house. And I don't remember us ever having to lay out any money on - on improvements. And my mother used to do all the decorating anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if your father used to dress you or bath you or read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, he didn't bath us - my mother used to do all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, he used to read a lot to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes he did. And he used to make us read out of books that he'd got for us.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he take you out without your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes he did, he used to take us o
ut in the morning before it got light, to look at birds. And my mother didn't like us going so early, she was frightened that people would think we were wrong - to - to allow the children to go out so early. My brother and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your father look after you when your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have any jobs to carry out around the house regularly to help your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, I used to help her all the time. You mean when I'd left school do you? Or when there wasn't any school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And other days as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, then I used to - wash the dishes and things, and help with the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you still carried on doing this after you left school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I did, I did more then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your brother help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes, he did, they were quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if you helped your brother with things he found difficult, like putting his clothes on or feeding him, when he was little?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't remember that. I do
n't remember having to help him but I was very careful of him. I was ached after him as he went to school. But as far as I know you know, he used to be able to do - other things on his own quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he help you with things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, he did. We were very close friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they expect you to go to bed at any particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
I don't know, I think - yes, we did used to go to bed - fairly early, we weren't on our feet late. But I have - I have no recollection of having to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your mother put you to bed as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes she did, but very quickly - we learnt to go on our own without any help at all. That was as soon as we were big enough. But my mother used to put us to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How old were you when you first went on your own, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I don't know, about eight I suppose. Something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you share a bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, we had two beds in one bedroom. My brother had a little bed of his own and I was in the big bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, they were in - a room of their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have a special room to have a bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No we didn't, we had a tub in front of the fire, that's how we had a bath. And we had a bath on the Saturday night, as a rule that is.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about having clean clothes? Did you have clean clothes on a Saturday too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes, we did after we'd had a bath, and we used to change. You know, apart from when you'd had some sort of accident.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about the family's meals, where did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh in the - the living room. We very rarely ate in the back, you know, we didn't have a fire in there, so we ate in the front nearly all the time. You know where Dunnadeg is don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh in the small kit
chen. Well she had an old - fashioned oven. And we had that for years and then oil stoves came. And then she had an oil stove and the old oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When did you usually have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 About eight to half past eight. Before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was everyone there or had your father already gone to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well my father had gone to work. He got up at five, and he had to leave before six and so of course he had to have food on his own then. But my mother used to get up, to - to start him off. And it was seven o'clock when he reached - Croesor quarry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he work in Croesor quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And he worked in Rhosydd too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What did you usually have to eat for breakfast or to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I'm afraid you had too much tea. We used to get mi
lk, and we used to have butter milk. But I'm sure it was milk when we were younger and buttermilk afterwards. And then we came to like tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What did you have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well we didn't get very much because we weren't near a butchers shop. But - we 
used to have bacon sometimes. We used to get bacon in the evening quite often, when my father came home. In those days we used to buy say a quarter of a pig and hang it up and that was - our main sort of meat, except for on Sundays, and then we'd have fre
sh meat, that was on the Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you ever have a special breakfast on a particular day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, it was always the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What did you have, did you have bacon for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No. No we didn't, we had an egg maybe. Or we'd have oatmeal b
read, if there was any you know. But nothing elaborate. Maybe we'd have marmalade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well we used to have a quarryman's dinner. After my father got back from work, so we had you know, dinner in the evening. You know, in the midd
le of the day when we came back from school well - we just had something and away we went again you know. We didn't eat at school, 'cos you know we were near enough to come home. We only ate in the evening really, you know, they call it a quarryman's dinn
er.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you said you used to have bacon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, bacon or ham and we make some sort of pudding, when there were blackberries around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your father take his food to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes he did, in a tin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What did you say you ate at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh something very similar to breakfast. What did we have I wonder. Jam or cheese or something, you know, that was at midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you had a special dinner on Sundays, do you remember if your mother or father baked bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, my mother did all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she bottle fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she make wine or medicine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, she didn't make wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, she used to make that sometimes. I remember her making one - sort of medicine out of blackberries and some sort of spices in it, you know, with the juice of blackberries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was this for colds and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right. And we used to have a sort of - drink made up o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 
f different sorts of leaves. Dio}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 d dial. And that was for when there something wrong with your stomach, and she used to make that, but she didn't make - wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Nor beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if your mother and father grew their own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well - yes, they did, they used to grow all their potatoes, well early potatoes anyway. And we had gooseberries and - and - rhubarb in the garden, you know, up above the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they buy any fruit and vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Very few really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember any tinned or dried fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Only bottled ones. No, I don't remember them in tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they keep any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No. Only when my father was very young, you know, before he married. At his home that is. My mother was the same with the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How many days in a week would you have meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 Well we ra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
rely had it you know, in the week, but we had it every Sunday. That's fresh
 meat. And when my father wasn't working or they were very expensive then we'd have to have New Zealand or foreign meat, because it was cheaper, and that's what we used to have on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Only you had bacon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, we used to have - some sort of bacon every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember any tinned meat at all? Like corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, we used to have salmon, and corned beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if you ever got extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, my father used to poach, and he'd get the odd phea
sant and the odd rabbit. And he felt he had a right to do this and nobody had the right to stop him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 On whose land did he poach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh, on the land - where my mother had - was born, on - on - on my grandmother's - land. And - some - you know, that 
was where he usually poached, or else he went to the - the land of Wern. He got permission to go there, but he was a poacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he do this often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes he did, he had great pleasure with the gun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food in order that the family should have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes I do. Yes, I remember that well. And I also remember me wanting more meat and my mother telling me no. We couldn't afford it. That was the time when my father wasn't working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember seeing your father having more than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No he didn't. Less in fact - if anything because he wanted us to have it. They wanted the children to have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were you allowed to talk at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes. Only - except for wh
en - my grandfather was there. And if grandfather was there then he'd - he'd look at us fiercely, there was no use in us talking - when we were eating that was. But we never made too much noise, you know, just talked to each other, you know, just like we 
are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Could you choose what you wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, we couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You had to eat everything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I can't actually remember ever leaving anyth
ing. But my brother wasn't very - strong and he couldn't really eat as much as say I did. And he used to have malt and things to make it up, because he had a weak chest you see, and he used to have amlt and I didn't 'cos I was O.K.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you wait until it was offered?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no, we helped ourselves. Everyone you now, through each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, we did. And we did - we had one, you know, if there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they expect you to hold the knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they did. And we had to use them too, as early as possible, you know, when we were very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have to sit in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't think so, not specially. Only sort of ordinary you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about bringing toys or books to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no, there was nothing like that on a table at mealtimes. Only afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Could you leave the table when you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You didn't ask to be excused or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 We just got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did all the family sit down at the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And did you always sit in the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your mother serve the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she do it in any sort of order, your father first and then you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, she - it was the same for everybody, for all four of us. She didn't give my father anything different and - nor did
 she give it to him any earlier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember where your brother sat before he was old enough to feed himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I don't remember, except for the little chair - up by the table. And we've still got that too. I remember him in this little chair.
 You know, the ones like they have now, except that it was old fashioned. But apart from that I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your mother feed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, when he was very small, but very quickly he was able to feed himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember how old he was when he joined the family at the table to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh about a year and a half to two I should think.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say your mother was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, she did. She was very friendly to everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Could you share your worries with her if you had any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes, we could - worries or pain. But we couldn't discuss anything like sex with her. Nothing like that in those days. She didn't even tell - me tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 t, you know, that I would be un}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 well. That I'd have periods. I had to find out myself. Nothing like that. But I was never frightened of telling her if something else was worrying me. You know, I was very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was your father easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes. My father was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, he did. And we were very happy - all the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
sort of tinned fruit and jellies. And if it was fine well my mother would take the table outside and we'd have our - tea in the garden, and children would come to - to tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You mean children from the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right, you know around my age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did - you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, we did, little things. Just simple things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about Christmas Day, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of day was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh well we were very happy 'cos we'd have got everything that could - afford to give us. We'd have presents in our stockings and on the bed and we were very happy at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have a goose or turkey or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well we used to usually have a pheasant you see. And if we couldn't have a pheasant, but usually my father saw to it that we did have one, we'd have a lump of beef or something. Or a piece of pork. And I don't know 
if I told you but when they used to buy - a half a pig or - a quarter of a pig there was a lot of pork as well - apart from the bacon. And - you know, that was the only time that we used to have - fresh meat apart from on Sundays you know, when we bought 
this - this big piece.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, we had an organ and a violin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Who played them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 My father used to play both of them. And I played the organ after. But my father taught himself to play the v
iolin. And he taught himself to play the organ too. I mean he wasn't very good, he wasn't an expert or anything, but he could do it well enough to teach us to sing and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did anyone in the family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, my mother and father sang, and t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 hey used to win in the Eistedfod}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 ds before they got married. One of the cups is up over there. I think he won that one singing in Liverpool.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about you and your brother, did you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, we sang too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember having a musical evening with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes. Very often. You know when there was a - a - an eistedfodd in the area. Well everyone would come to our house to practice you see. And my father used to teach the children - teach the children to sing and sort of train choirs, little ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if your - parents played games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they did you know little ones like snakes and ladders and draughts and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if there were any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, there were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well, literature books and - sort of autobiographical books really, rather than novels. Except that we did have Daniel Owen's novels, all of them in fact. They were all, you know, pretty good books in fact. You 
know, as many as my father could afford to get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were they Welsh books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes, they were. And - and then we had - a Cymiucoh, Red Wales, or the Bed Welsh. And that came out monthly and that was a pretty good book. And he got those and he sort of - 
put covers on them. You know, O.M. Edwards was the editor of that, and mostly those dame, you know, to the house every month. And so we had quite a few periodicals coming in. Sort of Welsh magazines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you said that all the books were Welsh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, they were all Welsh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well we used to get - the Banner. Y Fanenner it was called. But we never had a daily English newspaper like you have today. We did have the Rhedegywdd though, the Courier. And - Y - Cymro, the Welshman, we used to get those.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you ever remember seeing your mother and father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, they used to read every day. My father used to read his Bible every day, apart from reading books, and the ones that came in monthly. And the newspa
pers. My father was a great reader. He read more than my - my mother, although - you know, my mother read too but she didn't have very much time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember them reading out aloud to each other or to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, they did, they used to tell st
ories out - out - out of the Bible. They used to do that when we were small. But very quickly we were able to read ourselves you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember a funeral in your family when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes I do. Yes, the first funeral I remember - is my grandfather's funeral. I was ten then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember what sort of ceremony it was? Do you remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, quite well. Yes, my father died - my grandfather died in Penrhyn. And of course the - it was all coaches then, they didn't have a
ny carriages. And I was looking forward to getting a ride from Penrhyn to the - cemetery, far more than I thought about my grandfather. And I had black clothes in order to go to the funeral. I remember the clothes quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you remember them wearing armbands and hatbands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, I remember that, I mean that went on 'til fairly recently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 How was the c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 offin transported?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh in a hearse, you know, it was just a sort of - cart really. There was no glass or anything round it. And pull
ed by horses. And then we had the landau, and we sat in that. And I remember coming down that big hill, you know - the - out of - Penrhyn towards Lanfrothen and the - the - the wheels of this thing were making an enormous noise, squeaking. And I thought i
t was an enormous treat, I didn't understand that my grandfather had gone or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember going to visit friends, neighbours or relatives with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go with both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, and to both sides of the family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember going shopping with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, you know to the shops around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go with your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember going out with your father by himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh well I was telling you, we used to go out in the mornings. Because my father was very interested in nature. And - and then - apart from that, you know, if it was a holiday or something, we had a holiday and he happened to h
ave a holiday 'cos it was Labour Day or something, all four of us would go taking food with us. You know, mainly it was around here, we didn't really travel that far. We never went away anywhere. We never had holidays. But - we did go on a Sunday school t
r
ip, and we'd go to Barmouth or Pwhelli. Just for the day that would be. But apart from that you know we didn't - didn't go on holiday, except for one time that - I went to Liverpool to see my mother's sister. That was when we were seeing someone off to Am
erica, but apart from that we never went far to have a holiday or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of things did you do when you went on a trip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh you know, we swam and - messed around, I mean nothing very much. Wandered around the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you spend your Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh - it was just the same as any other day really, 'til I got older and I went out with other girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you play though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, or we'd go to the garden with my father. But it wasn't particularly differen
t, except obviously you didn't go to school. Yes, we didn't go to school. And we used to play around with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh it was chapel on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go three times?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you wear Sunday clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes. Yes, we wore our best clothes to go to chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about playing or working on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh no, we couldn't play. We just - we didn't think about it, you know, we - we couldn't play. We could go for a walk though. The thing was I mean we 
were frightened of playing. Not frightened of my mother and father, but frightened of the man next door. Because if he saw us playing, he'd look at - give us a - an incredibly black look. I mean my parents didn't prevent us but - we just never thought abo
ut doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your parents go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How often did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh my fa
ther went three times, and the children went three times, but - my mother stayed home on Sunday mornings to make the dinner. But she went to Sunday school and to chapel in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you went on Sunday school trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember any other activities that were organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, there was a Sayat. There was one every week, on a - Thursday. And then there was what we called the - the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 s meeting, the Band of Hope, and we used to go to all those. And tha
t was really the only entertainment we had. There weren't any pictures or anything. And we were glad to be able to go. Specially - especially the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 s meeting, and we'd have a sort of small scale eistedfodd. We'd sing and recite, and things like that you know every week. And - and very often - the - the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 s meeting was at Llwynon in Llanfrothen. You know where Llwynon is don't you? That's where the - the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 s meeting used to be. But before that it was in Plas Brondanw, where Clough Willia
ms Ellis now lives. But that was before Clough Ellis came to live there you see. Because - and - and after his father - had it - because there were two or three families living there then, and the - and the - children - the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 s meeting was there, Band of Hope, you know, for a spell, when I was very small. But as I got older the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 s meeting was at Llwynon, you know, Llwynon chapel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you belong to the choir at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you compete with the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was there another sort of temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, there was a temperance club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you remember going to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes I did. Yes, people - you know, adults and children went to that. And - those were called - temperance meetings an
d those were in the chapel, you know in Selow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were you a member of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of things did you do with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well they used to - pressure young people not to start - drinking, and so keep apart from drinking a
nd to sort of preserve your morality. And it was much more then you know than say now. And I'm sure it did have some effect too. I'm sure of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you belong to any other sort of club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't remember anything else. Anything other than those that I've mentioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if you said grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, we did sometimes, but not regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Who said grace?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember saying your prayers before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes we did, every night since we were able to speak. My brother and me. And my mother and father of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about family services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well, yes, we used to do that at the time of the - revival. But after the revival then - the whole thing sort of died down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes. Yes he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And his ideas were Labour and Nationalist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You see, to start off he was - he was Labour. But the - the Blydd hadn't started then. But it's af
ter - when was it - I think it was 1929 - he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 conscientious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453  member of the Blydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember why he was a member of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well, the things was in - at that time, I mean nearly all workers belonged to the Labour party. It was
 because he wanted to get - certain rights for the workers. And that was why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about your mother? What were her interests in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh - not the same as my father. She wasn't as keen. My father took more interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 But she was Labour was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Why was she Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I should think it was because she had the same ideas as my father. I expect it was my father's influence actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you remember your father or mother voting in the election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Before 1919. Well the thing is I remember them voting in every election. I don't know, had started with the Blydd at that time? But they always made sure that they went to vote.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you remember when your mother got the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes, I don't remember - but I mean after the vote came for women, well - she did then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they always vote Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I - I - I think my father may have voted Liberal - at the time when Lloyd George was on the sort - ascendant as it were. And it wa
s after that that he became Labour. And I mean the problem was around here there weren't any Labour candidates. Yes, yes, he had to vote Liberal. I remember Haydn Jones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Why did your father become Nationalist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well - I think it - I think he real
ized that - the principles he - he - he was fighting for within the Labour party - could - could - be better realized, if - Wales was - independent. The rights of - workers and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 In some areas men felt that they were in danger of losing their jobs or their houses if they voted differently from their employers?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I remember my father saying about this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember him being under this sort of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I remember some people being - turned out of their farms. Because they hadn't voted Tory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember your father being under this pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I remember my father's family. They - they thought they'd be able to buy this little farm you see, this is my
 father's family. And the thing was this Tory came along and - offered money sort of over their heads and although they'd been there for years - he got it. He - he gave - you know, he offered more money in order for him to get it. And my father felt very 
c
ross about - about that. And I know other people who were turned out of their farms you know, because they wouldn't vote Tory. They lived in Garregalltarn, it's a farm about - one and half miles from Llanfrothen. You know the farm of Garregalltarn, you kn
ow the one by the cliff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were your father and mother members of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, my father was. He was a member of Blydd.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember him working for the Blydd or for the Labour party at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't remember him doing anything special, only sort of talking to different people. But I don't reme}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 mber him taking a sort of promi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 nent part, going round canvassing or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 As he didn't do any sort of political activities apart from at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No, he didn't. Except that he belonged to the Blydd and he sort of gave things to the - Blydd. He gave money every year. I mean, apart from trying to influence people you know in conversations I don't remember him - actually doing anything else. But he w
as very committed to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well I mean - my father was so interested in nature, he'd spend a lot of time - walking around the area. He'd get so much pleasure out of going around, you know, up the tops - of the hills round here, and looking at different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he write anything about what he saw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Very little. No, he wrote very little in fact even though he did - go on - on the B.B.C. - a couple of times. And he wouldn't
 even write anything before that, you know, he just spoke from memory. No, he wrote very little in fact. He just wrote down a few notes you know. He didn't write like somebody like Ewen Brythyn. But he used to remember everything you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about your mother, did she have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You don't remember her going out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no, only when she went out with us. When we went on these trips and things. And of course she went to all the
 eistedfodds, because she used to sing herself before she got married, and so she got great pleasure out of going to the eistedfodds, and also training the children and they used to come to our home you know, when they were little, and they'd sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What time did your father get in in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he used to spend the evenings at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, except that he tried to go to the Sayat on - on Thursday evening. He'd go if if he could then, but it was a bit late for him 
to go really. And he used to go to the local meetings as well. He'd come to the Band of Hope if he could, to help out with the children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 He didn't go to any clubs or pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no, he didn't go to any pubs. But he did belong to a club, I 
think they were called the Raccobites. Yes, he - he belonged to that club. Yes, because - I remember them because if somebody }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 died who was related to the Racc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 obites then they used to wear these sashes, when they went to the funeral. It was like a sort of - well when you were ill you would get a certain amount of - money from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Like a sort of Friendly Society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right, it was a Friendly Society. Yes, it was a Friendly Society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember if your mother went to club or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your father take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did he go to the races or bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And your father belonged to a Friendly Society and he got money for sick insurance and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you get on with your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh, pretty well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Who did you play with as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You mean you want their names? Oh - just you know, girls of my age in the village. Always girls though, until 
I was about fourteen, and boys came into my life then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And they were girls from the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, you know, the ones from around.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Where did you usually play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh on the road and in the fields. We didn't have anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go to your friends houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes, yes, we did. And that's how we used to play at little house, you know, making little houses. And those would be up in the woods, out towards Plas you know, the little house would be sort of - away from the road. And we 
used to have things like - that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember any other games you used to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh we used to have fantastic games, I don't know if I can remember them though. We used to play five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 stones, and we used to play the games we had at school in - i
n - in the playtime. But we only had swings and things - outside you know in the evening. Out in the woods. And then we had - who comes, who comes, through the bridge - and the stars? Which was a sort of - oranges and lemons game. You know, two people wou
l
d stand with their hands - held high like a bridge and a whole row of people would go through. And then if we didn't - answer the question correctly then they'd catch us. And make us go behind them, and there were plenty more too if I could remember them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember playing quoits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't. Oh no, we didn't play quoits, but we used to play this game with squares Drawn in chalk on - on the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You mean hopscotch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that right, and skipping we used to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, we were, but I don't remember getting very dirty. But we could have done. I think we were really rather careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were you free to play with who ever you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 They didn't prevent you from playing with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you belong to any youth organisations at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No, only to these meetings I've talked about already. You know, belonging to the chapel. But there weren't any Guides or anything then. Not when I was small anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have any particular hobbies in your leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well mostly - I had piano lessons, and that took up a lot of my time in the evenings. And I used to learn on the organ we had in the house and then - as I got better I was a
llowed to go to school to practice. To practice on the piano in the school. And I used to get a lot of pleasure out of doing, you know, fancy work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Embroidery you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, embroidery and crochet - and knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you took an interest in animals and nature?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, in nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 With your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes. I think that was the most important thing really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have any pets at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh, only a cat. And sometimes we used to have a rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about collecting things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Di}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 d }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
no, we never collected birds eggs, we were never allowed to take an egg from the nest. My father wouldn't allow that. But we used to look for birds nests every - where. But - we - we used to keep very quiet about where they were becaus
e - if the children found out they would have destroyed them. I don't think I - collected anything though. Oh yes, dried flowers, you know, pressed in books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, I used to get great pleasure out of doing the little garden, you know, the one in he front of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember going fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, I used to go fishing, I had my own - fishing road. I - used to go with my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about biking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, but I was about fifteen before I got a bicycle. And then I used to use it to go to work - for many years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you take part in sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No no, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember going to theatres or concerts or to music hall when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I remember going to many c
oncerts, we used to have very big ones in the chapel and quite important people would come there. I once went into the theatre when I was very small in Liverpool, but I never went again, not to the theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, we we
nt there when we got big enough, but there weren't any pictures when I was small, not until I was in my teens in fact. But - there weren't - pictures except in Port Madoc or in - in Festiniog. And - I first went to the pictures when I was up in Festiniog,
 and I thought it was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was that at the Park cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No, it wasn't the Park cinema, there was a place where we went before that. You know, next door to what's it's name, I don't remember the street though. You know, the place where the S
alvation Army used to be, the - there's - there's a picture house there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, they did. But it was very little. They couldn't afford to give us very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you get it regularly though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes. Yes if we wanted to go somewhere. But they used to give us a penny or a ha'penny each every week to get sweets, but that was all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you spend it on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did anyone came to help your mother in the house at any time of trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh the only time they came was - at the birth of my brother, and a - at my birth too I think. Because of course nobody went to the hospital at that time. And an old wife from Pen - from Penrhyn used to come. She was called a midwife but she hadn't pass
ed anything. But she used to come and she came to my mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And that was the only help she had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And how did you manage when your brother was born, did your father do a lot of the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't think he did bec
ause an auntie came as well. Apart from this old lady - old lady. So it wasn't necessary for my father to do much more. But in those days they didn't stay in their beds very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes. Yes, in Llanfrothen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you see a lot of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they always used to come round to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go to their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes. They were friends with everybody as far as I know. 'Cos in those days the whole village was friendly. And - the people from out}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 sided too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And where did they usually meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh in each others houses. Except for, you know, chapel activities. Of course they meet each other at chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say that your parents shared the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they were all fairly similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your father or mother have any special friends of their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I'm sure, but they were friends - more friends with - some people than others. But 
mostly people who were closest - the closest relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 But - you don't remember any sort of of distinction between your mother's friends or your father's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no, except that you know - at the time of the Revival, my father used to invit
e people round to - to our house, people who had now where to got except into the hotel. And rather than let and allow them go into the hotels he'd - invite them home, you know, for a game of something. And then those people would become - you know, frien
ds and - and keep coming round, even after the Revival had gone. In fact our house was pretty popular for anyone, for people, you know, apart from - relatives.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You said your friends were invited did they invite their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes they would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they get offered something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, they never went from there without - being offered something to eat, or without having a meal in fact. I mean, people you know that came from quite far away. People who lived quite near didn't eat at home all that often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they come on any special days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh you know when there was some sort of holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say that the friends invited to the house were your father's friends or your mother's friends or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh they were friends of both, it was just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember friends coming round without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, a lot. They knew that there'd be a welcome always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did neighbours come too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 People tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, do you remember your father and mother with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes. I mean that's how it was. Yes, and me too because I mean - there weren't any pictures or anything, because the pictures started when I
 was in my teens you see. And you see things got organised through the chapel, like the Band of Hopes was our amusement. And we learnt things - for that you know. And specially they - the people came round to see my mother and father about music. And they
 came to our house to practice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have a sort of musical evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, very often. And everyone took their part.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You said that people came round to your house to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 People often divide soci
ety up into different classes or groups, would you say that in the period before 1918 that you felt that some people belonged to one class or group and others belonged to another one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No. Not at all. No, everyone was on the same level - as far as we were concerned anyway. That was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 But do you remember feeling that some people were big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 nobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes. Oh yes, I remember that. Specially the people from Nysfor, and I remember children, and men too, whenever they saw them coming they'd b
ow to them. Because they thought that they had to. Because people felt that they ought to put them a step above and they - they'd be the sort of people that we wouldn't - invite to our house, even if they would come. They felt that they were above - a ste
p above.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember any other families that you felt were a step above?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well they're the main people. Because the people fr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 
om Plas weren't her then. The W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 illiams Ellis'. No, I only remember this one family that was like that, you know, in this area. People who felt that they were something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say that the ordinary people were all the same level then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And obviously you belonged with the ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of people would you say that the Nysfor people were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well I'm sure they were rich, you know, and they were much better off than us. And they - they felt in themselves that they couldn't mix - mix with us. But I mean they weren't sort of spiteful to anyone. Only that they felt that they were somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of people were the ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well, I'd say that - we were all - happy, and we were all - sort of - close to each other. Everybody was sort of one. Especially - you know, people who went to chapel
. People were sort of one together. There was no sort of ill feeling between us. Even with the people from the church there wasn't. Even they, I mean we all went to the Michel meetings, you know, even the Baptists from the other chapel here. Everybody was
 together, and they could all pull together properly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember being brought up to respect some people differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No I don't. I was brought up to respect everyone - the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You say you had to bow or curtsey to some people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well it wasn't that we had to. But - everybody did. You didn't feel you had to but you saw everyone else doing it, which made you think that you ought to. But nobody sort of said, remember to do it. But you know, like kids are we saw other peop
le doing it and everyone sort of copied each other. But the - the men used to raise their hats or - or bow like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you only do it to the Nysfor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I don't remember anyone else from this area. And you see the - Clough Williams Ellis' family wasn't here when we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You don't remember seeing the employers of the quarry and having to show respect to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no, we didn't, because my father didn't get on with them. Especially the man - in charge, because he - he ha
ted him. He felt that he wasn't - treating the workers properly. So obviously he'd never invite him to our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you ever remember saying sir to anyone or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No I don't. No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember what you used to call people, did you say Mrs and Mr.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, we always called them by their surname. Except for - you know, very close friends and of course relatives. And we'd call them by their first names of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you ever remember anyone saying sir to your parents or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Who would you say were the important people in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well you mean - people that I thought were important? Well we counted the - preacher as important and the schoolmaster. I don't remember anyone, apart from the Nysfor people, we didn't really count them as - as particularly important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you come into contact with the teachers and the ministers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, we saw them all the time. Because we went to chapel. And the schoolmaster was very - commit
ted to the chapel too. So therefore we mixed with them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know why you considered these people important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well you see they had a higher status than the ordinary man, I mean the ordinary quarrymen. For one thing, they'd had more schooli
ng, and therefore we did count them as fairly important. And after all they taught us, particularly the schoolmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Who would you say the shopkeepers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh they had to mix in with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about the preachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh they mixed with everybody too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh he did too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about the farmers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well they were the same as us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And what about the employers, the quarry employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh you mean the people who were the bosse
s? The bosses of the quarry you mean? Oh they were all O.K. except for - this particular who owned the quarry, you know, the one that - my father really hated. He certainly didn't mix with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about the stewards, did they mix?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, because they were just ordinary people who'd worked themselves up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well - long ago they used to say that - people who'd done - who'd sinned the chapel went to the church. Well they'd call the sin
ners too, or people who'd - done wrong. I'm not saying it's like that now, but they used to say, oh well he's gone against the chapel, he'll go to church now. That's how they were then. And - and they'd call it - some people anyway would it call it the so
r
t of - chamber of sin or the chamber of wrong. But I mean obviously good people did go to the church, but if they'd done something wrong in the chapel they could still go to church, that was the thing. Even of they'd been thrown out of the society and no 
- were no longer a member of the chapel they could go to church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of people would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I don't know, they all went as far as I know. I only remember one or two people who didn't go to chapel, and those would carr
y on - Harvest Thanksgiving Day. I don't remember anybody who didn't go on Thanksgiving Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Would you say that in your area the ordinary people had the same standard of living amongst the ordinary people, or was there any great distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No there wasn't, very little in fact. Everybody was at the same standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You don't remember one group of people feeling they were superior to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember some families being called rough and others respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, they used to say, oh he's very - rough. And what they meant was that he was more keen on collecting money. Except I mean obviously there were respectable. But - you know, other people would sort of spend and be generous and enjoy thems
elves rather than - spend their money - rather than save their money. I think the problem is there that the - the Welsh words - the word for rough has two meanings, that's why it appears to be slightly contradictory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember a distinction being made between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You don't remember your father as he was a craftsman differentiating himself from other people in the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No they didn't you see, they were very good. Especially in the quarry. They w
ere so good at helping people who - came there from the beginning, you know, who were just starting. The craftsmen did their best to teach the others, even if it meant him wasting time himself he'd teach - other people, to become craftsmen. They didn't tr
ample on people because they weren't craftsmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say that your mother and father had the same attitude to people of different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say that your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular group or class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No. Except that she did belong to a sort of - county society, which - trained - children to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15013940\charrsid11547453 sing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 in choirs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 But she didn't see herself as belonging to the middle class or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no, no not at all. That was unknown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember people improving themselves in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well there were some people who - refused to go to the doctor, you know, they - they'd - they'd treat themselves, and make themselves better. By taking sort of homemade medicines and th
ings for their stomachs and that. And then they'd have something special for shingles. And there were other people who - reckoned that they could - treat shingles by blowing on it. But there was people who'd eaten a particular plant you see, and - I can't
 
remember who they were now, and then they used to blow on these shingles and they were supposed to be cured. There was a lot of sort of folklore about that, much more than there is now in fact. And the other thing that we used to think was that if childre
n
 had T.B., if they - took them up on a little railway towards Ffestiniog and - you opened the - the window of the train and allowed the smoke to come into the carriage and into their lungs, then it would be cured. I mean everybody thought that, they thoug
h
t it was right. And I remember taking my brother up there. Taking him up to Ffestiniog in order that he could go through the tunnel and, you know, get the - smoke into his lungs. There was a lot of sort of - mystical thoughts like that then. Much more tha
n there is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember people improving their status, through education or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh well, yes, a lot of ordinary people came on in the world, you know, having been to college and that. But they were just the same as us you
 know, even after they'd been to college it didn't change them, they didn't count themselves as any better than us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember anyone being called a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well they say that about several - good people. They say,
 you know, oh he's a real gentleman. But I can't name them for you but there were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know why they were called like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well it was because they treated you kindly. And they lived well - honourably. You know, that's what they mean when t
hey say real gentlemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh well we were frightened of the policeman. But I mean he didn't come round - round to us or anything, but it was something to do with his rank you know. I
 mean, we didn't do anything wrong, but - but despite that, you know, we were frightened of him. And people - children would tell each other you know, watch out for the policeman, and told each other that they were frightening and dangerous. But the only 
p
erson I was really frightened of was the truant officer, the attendance officer. It didn't matter how much they told me that he wasn't - fierce and - and cruel you know I would scream and cry - if he came to school. I thought he'd come to fetch me to take
 me off somewhere. But I was very small when I thought things like that. But I wasn't afraid of anyone else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How would you have thought a policeman treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I mean - since we lived in the country we didn't see any sort of great routs
 or rows, you know, nothing with drinking or anything. But if he did come we were frightened of him just - I mean it was something to do with his uniform.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well he lived next door to us you see. He was an uncle of ours you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You didn't see him as a landlord then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no. No, no, he was a cousin of my father's you see. No, I mean he didn't see him - himself as anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you ever remember your parents having trouble making ends meet, of keeping things going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, yes I do. I realized that when my father was out of work, and there wasn't any dole or anything. There was just the little amount that he got from the Raccobites. But it was just 
a few shillings. And my mother never complained either. Except that I know she had trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you feel about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I was old enough to - to feel a pity for them. But I never remember going completely without. We always had buttermilk 
and bread. Or something to fill us up. And I remember I was so keen on meat and my mother used to say, no, you can't have any. You can only have this much, until your father starts working again. But we did get, you know, some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you ever remember getting help from charity at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
If there was somebody in the area that people disapproved of tremendously was there any special way of showing this disapproval? In England there was a custom where people went round to the house of the perso
n they disapproved of and made a great noise outside, a sort of rough music ceremony?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes I know. No, I - I haven't any recollection of that here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember people making straw men or effigies of people they disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have any lessons at home before you went to school? From a private tutor or from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well I'm sure I'd learnt to say the A.B.C. before I went. 'Cos I went to school when I was three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 But you didn't have any formal lessons at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh - no. But I'm sure I could say the alphabet. And I expect I knew a few very easy words.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 But you were three when you actually went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go in the afternoon and in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes. Yes, I went all through the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What time did you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I had to be there by nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you come home at half past three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What sort of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well it was this school here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Mixed, boys and girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you walk to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How long did it take to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh, from Danydag, what was it, it was about what - ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Who did you go to school with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well with the children fro
m, you know, around. From the street of Penhyrw you know. You know, one or two of my friends maybe, and of course with my brother. But as he got older he went on his own. But I mean generally the children sort of went along together, or - you know, maybe 
in twos and threes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You said you came home to have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I thought the world of it, I never wanted to miss school. I wanted to go all the time. I think we were very lucky actual
ly because there was a very kind infant teacher there, and she was there for fifty years. And we used to do her hair and everything in the playtime and we used to play with her as is she was - well we were never frightened of her. And then the headmaster 
was the same. And he had - he commanded tremendous respect, I never saw him hit anyone. Even the oldes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
 boys showed respect to him. He had tremendous authority, without being unpleasant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 So obviously you felt O.K. towards the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes I did. I was great friends with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember the teachers emphasising that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well, you mean things like religion? Well they didn't really say very much about that. The only recollection I have is -
 is - is that - you know, and there's a lot of talk about it now, you know, about smoking. Well there was this chart up on the wall at school, and it was called something like the effect of smoking on the young. And the teachers would go up to that every 
n
ow and again and see if we remembered what it said on the chart, you know - what we were to do and what we weren't to do. And that did have an impression on me because I really did feel that smoking would kill me, and Mrs Jones used to ask us to answer - 
s
ome of the questions that were on this chart, and this used to come, you know, every now and again. But I don't feel that they used to sort of influence very much over belief, because the headmaster used to come to chapel - and take us at Sunday school yo
u see, which was quite different to what it was like at school. But they did teach us how to behave and not to be rude.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 They taught you manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they emphasise tidiness and being on time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about emphasising ways of speaking? Were you supposed to speak pure Welsh or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh well, there was quite a bit of English in the school. Sometimes he used to ask things in English, and then we'd have to reply in English. But it wasn't the same as when 
my father went to school because my father remembers the Welsh Knot. My father went to school at the time of the Welsh Knot in fact, and he also used to pay tuppence a week for his schooling, and he left there when he was twelve and went to the quarry you
 see. But you know, I don't remember anyone doing anything out of place as school because he was such a good man, the headmaster, and nobody went against him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You don't remember seeing him punishing or caning anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't ever remember seeing him do that. He never hit anyone. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was there any sort of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 detention or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453  lines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, yes, we had that. There were lines. But I never had them. Except that I do remember other people getting them. Oh well, for things like - well if they
'd made mistakes in their spelling. If they'd written something in English and hadn't spelt it correctly, they'd have to write the word out hundreds of times as far as I know. But he never kept them very long. He wasn't very hard at all. And he had a cane
 always sort of in evidence on his desk, and all he had to do was look at it, and everyone was frightened. But I never saw him use it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, they were very keen for us to do well at school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they ask you what you'd done at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did they go to the school to see the teachers or to see the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, well the things was that the - the headmaster used to come round to our house, 'cos he
 was friends with us you see. And then they used to her about us then. You know, he used to come round quite often you see to our house. But as far as I remember they didn't go to school to see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say that the other children in the school came from the same type of homes you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember the teachers singling out some children for different treatment to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I do remember one teacher there, who was rather cruel to the children, and roug
h with them. Not the headmaster. He might come up behind where they sat and then pull their ears or something. And the children were very frightened of him, although he never did anything to me. But the boys were frightened of him. But I've no recollectio
n apart - f - of anything apart from him being, you know, rather rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember any favourites in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no, I don't. I don't remember any favourites at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember any gangs in the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't 
remember. No, there weren't. But the thing is that I don't remember this but they use to say that the Rhydd children used to come down to the school here, you know, the big boys from Rhydd and then there'd be big boys from this side and they'd out over to
wards Glanwern, it's the sort of - low ground in front of Wern farm, and they'd fight out there. But I never saw that happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember some children being left out of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go to another school after this one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No I didn't. I was - in - Llanfrothen school there until I was fifteen. I - stayed longer than people did normally. And the thing was that it was me that refused to go to Ffestiniog school, to Balunau Ffestiniog, and - you see what - I de
cided that I wanted to go and work in a shop and - nothing else would do - I wanted to go to this shop because I wanted to learn to be a milliner, you know, making hats. And the thing was that I stayed on at the primary school until I got a place there, I
 
had to wait you see 'cos I was too young. And so I stayed on at school and I - used to help out with the younger children, if one of the teachers was ill or something. And then in the end I got a position teaching in Croesar school, which is a - a tiny - 
v
illage at the top of the valley, in which Llanfrothen is lower down. And - what happened was that I got a pretty good report from the headmaster and some forms were filled in in Ffestiniog and I was allowed to go as a supplementary teacher to Croesor and 
I
 was there for seven years. Because the - the doctor told me that the shop didn't suit me and I had to leave. And - you see, the - the report from the headmaster and from the - minister, was enough for me to be able to go to teach in Croesor. Obviously I 
don't think that would happen now, but it also depended on the report of the inspector. But he said everything was O.K. So I was there for seven years. And I used to go backwards and forwards on my bike every day. About - two mile - Uphill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you were fifteen when - you lefts school? Would you have stayed on if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you take part in any night school or anything like that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No I didn't. Oh yes, SI did go once. I used to go to some classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I can't remember. It was something to do with Literature. But I didn't take the class myself, but I went to a class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Looking back on your education do you have any regrets about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I don't, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 Do you think you benefit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 ed from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, I'm sure I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When you were in school did you have any part time jobs at all, something to get a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No. Not to get money I didn't. I only used to do things with the orga
n, you know, teaching people to sing and I'd play for them, but I didn't get anything for doing that. Oh yes I did. I - used to play in the chapel for years. And sometimes they'd give me a cheque for it. I used to play the organ in the chapel when I was t
welve years sold, until I married in fact. And I got a present when I got married. But I didn't have anything like a - apart time job that brought money in - I mean nothing regularly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you used to just play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I used to play all 
through the day on Sunday, from the - morning 'til evening. Until other children grew up and - and they could do it. But even then it was me that had to do it until I - got married. But - some other people did it in Sunday school for a spell, people who'd
 learnt it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you feel that you were fairly paid for this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
And - you know, I never felt - well I only got about two pounds or two pounds ten for teaching in Croesor, in a month. And I didn't see it as - as too little. It must have been beca
use things were so cheap, and I used to get clothes with that and give some to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 But when you played in the chapel did you feel you were being fairly paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I didn't expect anything then. I felt it was my duty. In fact I was rather pr
oud of being able to play there. Especially when I was only twelve years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When you got money from the chapel did you give it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, not specially. I used to give a bit to my mother every month though. But when I got money that w
ay I used to - save it to buy - a bike or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you played - enjoyed playing the piano in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And was that the only thing you did before you left school in the way of earning some money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I didn't do anything else apart from that and go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh this was in the millinery in Penrhyn. I was learning to be a milliner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I went there you know to see if they had 
a place. And the thing was you - see I wasn't allowed to become a milliner, for two years you see, and so I used to just serve in the shop. And learn the trade as it were, and then the first world war came And then I had to help in the grocery part. I was
n
't supposed to do that though. And I only got half a crown a week then, and I had to help out in the grocery bit. All the time that I was supposed to be learning to become a milliner. Learning to make these hats. And then - once I was able to make sort of
 patterned hats - patterned hats then I got ten shillings a week. That was the - biggest wage that I had in fact, you know, in that job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you start when you were fifteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I was just sixteen when I started there, and I was there for about 
three years. But just when - at the time when I was earning ten shillings, the doctor - told me that I had to leave. I was too much sort of - amongst clothes and things, and that it wasn't - healthy for me. And I had to leave, and it was at that time that
 a vacancy arose in Croesor and the headmaster here said, oh well, why don't you try for that job? And you're sure to get it, he said. And then I went to teach in Croesor. And I was there until 1923 when I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What hours did you work in Penrhyn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh I worked from nine in the morning 'til eight o'clock at night. And on Saturday night was there until after ten o'clock. Yes, until it was after ten. And I didn't get anything extra for working overtime or anything. And then nothing for Sunday, 
I didn't work on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you get a half day at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, we got a half day on Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have holidays with pay at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes? I think I got a week, or - yes, it was a week, with pay that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you got half a crown to start with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you feel that this wage was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well the things was I so wanted to make these hats that I didn't complain about the wages. But my mother always said to me that - she didn't think it was enough. And I
 used to suffer there quite a lot, my legs used to swell up any everything, because I was on my feet too much, and I never used to tell my mother that in case she made me leave the shop you see. I did like it there, even though I didn't get the wages I wa
nted, and I didn't complain somehow. I was so pleased to get something I wanted to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well, I had to make, you know, the shapes out of - buckram. Buckram. And - and then cover them with silk and things like th
at. And I had to make wedding hats and things like that, you know, patterned hats. There was a milliner who had experience in London there you see and - she used - was the head milliner, and she was quite a good person for me to learn from. And I wanted t
o do it, and of course when you want to do something then - of course you do it much better.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you give any of the money that you earned in Penrhyn to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No I didn't because really it wasn't enough for me to get clothes. And I had a 
bike and of course there were certain costs with that. No, my poor mother didn't get anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you get on with the people you worked with in Penrhyn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh very well, I was - very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well he w
as a bit mean actually. To tell you the truth. You know, we were supposed to be allowed to sit down if there wasn't a customer in, but he always made sure that he had something extra for us to do. He made us tidy something, so that we didn't waste any tim
e at all. He was very very keen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you feel towards your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well I was a bit sort of angry at him when I saw him - when I felt he was being too keen. And one things was I used to want to leave there, sometimes when I was playing in s
ome meeting, and he wouldn't let me go, you know, only just at the end, for a few minutes. And the he wasn't even - very - willing for me to go. He begrudged me just - just because I asked to go. He wasn't all right, but the assistants were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you feel towards the work itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I was very happy with it. That's why I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And then after three years you went up to Croesor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 I think it was three. I think it was about three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What exactly did you have to do in Croesor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
I had to teach the infants. There were three different classes that we had. Had standard one and standard two and the little ones. And there was no partition at all in the school so it was fairly chaotic. And Mr Davis was up the top and - all in 
all there was quite a lot of noise on both sides. It was very difficult to work without a partition, but we did it O.K.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How many teachers were there there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh there was just the headmaster and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What hours did you work, sort of school hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes. Only school hours, and then of course I had school holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you get paid in the holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You said you got paid two pound ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I think it was about that. Two pounds ten a month that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You said before that you felt that this was O.K.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes, I don't remember complaining about it. I could just give a bit to my mother and get clothes. I mean things were so cheap in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you get on with Mr Davis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh I was very close fri
ends with him. He helped me a lot because I hadn't had any experience before, you know, when I started. He told me what to do and things. And because I was sort of used to singing, well I took, the music for the whole school and he wasn't very keen on sin
ging.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How did you feel about being a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh I was very happy, you know, the friends - the children were friends with me and they came to meet me and things. I was never unhappy there, and I went there you know in every weather. And I remembe
r going there once or twice and I couldn't get into the school 'cos there was snow up to the top of the door. And I used to go there in all weathers. The only thing I was fright}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 ned of was the bull on the road. On the way there, you know, up by Park, and t
he road was so narrow and there was nowhere to jump out of the road when I saw the bull coming. That was the only thing I was fright}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 ned of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You didn't work after that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no, I didn't. No, I didn't work after I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you have liked to have done another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no, I wouldn't, I was quite happy as I was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you served an apprenticeship at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh no, only in the shop as a milliner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You didn't do any sort of training for being a teacher? You just went straight in didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes, that's right. Because of course I'd had quite a good report. And I had to fill in these forms for - well it must have been Dolgethau for the County, for the Education - Authority, you know, to see - so that they coul
d see how much I knew. And I got it quite quickly and easily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No I didn't. I don't think I was offered actually, I don't think there was a union for supplementary teachers then. There was only one for the headmasters as far as I remember, at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Would you say that employers and workers see the world in the same way, that they have the same interests or do you think that there's a conflict between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well here wasn't - at that time, there 
was nothing similar to what there is now. I mean, if anything I don't think they complained enough about their wages in those days. They just used to take it quietly, there was no - mention of strikes, except for once in the quarry when they struck for mo
re money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember anything about that strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh well, nothing apart from the fact that the employers were very very hard. Oh but I do remember there was enormous strike in Bethesda, and - and people were - on strike for months and months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You mean at Penrhyn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes. Yes. And everyone was, you know, on charity. But I never remember it getting as bad as that here. But there was a strike, and I remember once my father and a - crowd of other people got together at lunchtime to discus
s the strike, and Mr Kellow, the owner, saw them and they got a terrific row. Even though it was in their own free time. And my father was very - angry towards Mr Kellow after that, because he didn't treat the workers as he should.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Mr Kellow was the owner manager was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes, that's right and he used to live up in Bryn in Croesor. In Croesor. And a sister of his used to live in the village, and an auntie too at Mean Avon. Do you remember Ninafon, when you were up in - in Garegvald, you know, when
 you used to live up - up round here. You know that little bungalow, you know the one. Arthur Williams or something lives there now, and she was related to Kellow, and her husband was related to my father you see. But my father was pretty angry with him r
i
ght 'til to end. He felt that the didn't treat the workers properly. He wouldn't allow them to discuss things, and they were only doing it in their lunch hour too, but that wouldn't do. And I remember you know, he was worth millions and millions and my fa
ther always used to say - that it was the - the workers money that he had, because he hadn't given enough to the workers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you ever feel that there were any distinctions amongst the workers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No. They were very close to each other, and very much - of the same mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you've already answered the one about craftsmen haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you yourself, you never felt that you respected craftsmen more than ordinary workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I didn't make any distinction - not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Would you say that starting to work full time changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well - I felt really that I was more sort of - responsible really when - once I started work, and I liked to - to be able to contribute s
omething to the family, although I didn't get enough to be able to do that in Penrhyn. But I only did feel that, you know-, I had more responsibility and I was helping them live. Oh yes, I certainly felt that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You lived at home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes I did. I was at home until I married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did starting to work full time change your relationship you're your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, no, it didn't, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And not with your brother either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you spend Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You still went to Sunday school and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Yes. Yes. Everything was the same. Oh yes, but I must say that while I was in Penrhyn - O couldn't come and play in the chapel - so often. And - you know, I couldn't get back - so - 
so often to go to chapel, and I didn't want to belong to the chapel in Penrhyn, although I did come back here on a - on a - a Sunday night when I could. Because I always intended to come back to Llanfrothen to live, and - once I did come back I went, you 
know, back to chapel regularly, although I didn't take up playing again. Although - except that I didn't go in the - in the morning so often because I used to make the dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you take an interest in politics? What were your views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh they we
re the same as my father's, I think this was because we read the same papers. And I'd done this since I was very young. I was a member of the - Welsh Nationalist party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were you in the Labour party before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I was, yes, but obviously I d
idn't have a vote. Because I mean I didn't - you know, votes for women didn't come until when - which year was it - oh I think it was 1928, and when the vote did come, when I could vote - I gave my vote to the Blydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know why you s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 mpathised with the Blydd?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Well, I'm sure it was because of the things that I'd read at home you know. The ideas that I'd picked up from - from the magazines and the books at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you ever feel you were under any pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I was quite sure of my beliefs. And I didn't do it because my father did. It was just that I was of the same opinion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Were you a member of the Blydd?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you work for the Blydd at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, I did a bit. I used to do a bit. I don't remember what though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you do anything apart from at election times? Did you go round talking to people or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I never took any part in any sort of talking or meetings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you change the way you spent your free time after you started working full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No, I didn't. But the thing was I was courting the boy I eventually married. And I used to go out every night with him you know, and go for a walk - at every opportunity. You know, apart from
 doing a few things in the house, sewing and - but I didn't do any sport of part time job or anything. But we used to go out a lot with the bikes, and we'd go pretty far for a - for a drive - for a ride. I used to get a lot of enjoyment out of riding abou
t the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you go out in the evening with your friends? To Penrhyn to the pictures or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
No, well there weren't pictures you see. No, very little. I did very little apart from the meetings we had, you know, the chapel meetings, and
 the small eistedfodds. And I - became friendly with my - husband, when I was very young, and therefore I didn't really go out very much with other friends. You know, I didn't go out with them although I was friends with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have other friends apart from your husband, did you make new friends in Penrhyn for instance or up in Croesor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh yes, yes, I mean I had lots of boyfriends - and girls in Penrhyn, ones that I didn't know from before, and - of boys from Penrhyn tool. And I'm sure I wouldn't have met them unless I had gone to Penrhyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes, I bought all my friends home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And you met them through work and things did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Is there anything special that you used to do with boyfriends or girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Not specially, I mean I was very fond of wandering about the mountains, and going for very long rides if there was a holiday. We might do about fifty miles, with the bike. But I don't remember anything else. But 
you know, he used to live in - in - in - on a farm and so I used to go up to the farm quite often, and help with the hay. You know the - from - that farm way up above the Aberglachan Pass.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 So your husband was Frank's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's right. 
Yes, he was Frank's brother. You know Frank don't you, but of course he's gone now hasn't he. Yes, my father was great friends with him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 You said your parents met your friends, did your parents always expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh yes they 
did, and they'd ask where we'd been. And I never, you know, didn't tell her, and she did sometimes say if I'd been out late you know, well I would like you to be in a bit earlier but she didn't get angry. And I always used to let them know who I was with 
and I used to take other boys home you know, apart from my husband. And my mother really preferred me to take them home rather than go out without saying who I was going with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What time did they expect you to be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well they expected me in by ten o'clock. But in the summer it was often eleven, especially if we'd been far away somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Did you have any children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How many did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh we only had one child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh he keeps the youth hostel in Mant Gwynant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What jobs has he done all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh, he hasn't been at the youth hostel. He was very unlucky. See, he started off - becoming a mate to his father as an electrician. Because you see my husband used to work for Manweb, T
he Merseyside and North Wales Electricity Board, he didn't stay in farming although he was a son of a farmer, and he started as my father's mate, but he los}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453  his health. He went to help his aunt on the farm and he did too much, because they didn't have any servants there. And he got pleurisy you see, and that developed and became T.B. and he was in the san}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 torium for months and months. And the thing was that - after he came out of the san}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 torium the last time, well the doctor said that he shouldn't go back to Manweb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How old was he when he came out of the san}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 torium the last time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
You mean the last time? Oh he got married the last time he came out. Wait a minute, he's forty-three now, and the - the eldest girl is fourteen and she was born just after he came out of the san}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 torium. She's fourteen, nearly fifteen no. And since then you see he's been a warden in the youth hostel. Him and his wife, you know, they're co-wardens.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 When did they start that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well they started off at Caddafydd,
 an other youth hostel you know, 'cos - it's closed down now but it used to be there. In fact he'd gone to Caedafydd before he went to the san}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 atori}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 um the last time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How long did he work for Manweb?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh he did that before. He went to the youth hostel and before he went to the san}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4868158\charrsid11547453 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 torium.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know roughly how many years he was with Manweb?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 No, I'm afraid I can't remember you know, I can't say in a minute. But he was there for - quite a few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about when he worked on the farm with your aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh well he went there before he got the job with Manweb you see. You know, he went to work at Hafodlyowfog, which is a farm in the Mant Gwynant Valley, beyond Bed Gelet. It's an isolated farm. And the thing was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Was that when he was fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
Oh no, no, he - he'd just matriculated you see, he'd done well enough to go to agricultural college. And the thing was he went to do a bit of practical experience oh his aunt's farm. And he was doing that you see before he went to 
agricultural college. And the thing was that he lost his health during that time, they say he did too much, carrying great big cans of milk because they were short of servants there, and the result was that he lost his health. But he was quite all right b
e
fore that. And he went to hospital in Machynlleth and he came back and he went back to Machynlleth and then he went down to South Wales. There's a big sanaitorium down there I forget what it's called. Anyway further down from Aberystwyth. And the thing wa
s
 what they didn't understand was that he'd got - T.B. had spread to his kidneys and they were just treating him for T.B. of the lung, and then they found out, and they realized he had a T.B. kidney, a T.B. gland on his kidneys and had to take one of his k
idneys out, and since then well he's been at the youth hostel, at least his his own master there, he can do roughly what he likes. But he doesn't work very hard there. But he's in quite a good place really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What was your brother's work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Oh well h
e started off with a solicitor in Port Madoc. He was a clerk you know with a solicitor. And then he got a place as a traveller for David Jones in Liverpool, you know, distributing groceries. And then he left David Jones and went to Jacobs was a traveller,
 and then he bought his own coal business in Conway that was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you remember for how many years he did all these different jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well he was about two or three years in Port Madoc. He went away when he was eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 How long was he with David Jones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well I'd say that between - Jacobs and David Jones he was there about eight to ten years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And then he got his own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 What about your husband, what were his jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Well he spent most of hi
s life with Manweb. But he did do some work with - you know, in the collieries in South Wales. And he did do a - a job as a gardener in Plas Aberglaslyn, and in Plas Oerddwr, just as an ordinary worker you know. And then he got a job with Johnson and Phil
ips, who were the same thing as Manweb you know but before Manweb. And that was the time when they were starting to put up all the electricity lines here, and Johnson and Phillips had got the contract and he worked for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Do you know how old he was when that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 
He was about twenty-six when - he started with these, and then Johnson - Johnson and Phillips left the area and rather than go away with them he got a job immediately with Manweb, and to start off he was a mate and then he became 
a linesman by the end, with Manweb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13840783 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 And that's what he did was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12988738 LH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8607006\charrsid11547453 Yes, that's what he did until he got ill.
